7804 /******************************************************************************/
7805 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32L0xx device product */
7806 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
7807 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
7808 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
7809 /* product lines within the same STM32L0 Family */
7810 /******************************************************************************/
7811 
7812 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
7813 
7814 #define LPUART1_IRQn RNG_LPUART1_IRQn
7815 #define AES_LPUART1_IRQn RNG_LPUART1_IRQn
7816 #define AES_RNG_LPUART1_IRQn RNG_LPUART1_IRQn
7817 #define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
7818 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
7819 
7820 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
7821 #define LPUART1_IRQHandler RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler
7822 #define AES_LPUART1_IRQHandler RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler
7823 #define AES_RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler RNG_LPUART1_IRQHandler
7824 #define TIM6_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler
7825 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
7826 
7835 #ifdef __cplusplus
7836 }
7837 #endif /* __cplusplus */
7838 
7839 #endif /* __STM32L073xx_H */
